  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The clinical effects of intra-operative radiofrequency ablation in patients with persistent
      or permanent atrial fibrillation and an indication for an implantation of a heart valve
      prosthesis or coronary bypass surgery are the purposes of this study. The study will examine
      if and to what extent the quality of life and the use of medical care differs between
      patients with and without ablation. Furthermore, there will be thorough echocardiographic
      examinations of the heart to detect differences between the different treatment groups. The
      patients will be followed for one year after treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
